* â¢Preventionâ¢ means carrying out measures aimed at mitigation of disaster and possible damage;
* â¢Damage caused by disasterâ¢ means the total loss the country, local area, enterprises, organizations and population, caused by suffering peopleâ¢s health, lives, the loss of livestock, animals, property and the environmental pollution in disaster;
* â¢Disaster siteâ¢ means the territory where limitations are imposed because of a disaster, and wherein the rescue and response activities are undertaken;
* â¢Disaster warningâ¢ means the dissemination of signals and warning information regarding the danger of a disaster to the population;
* â¢Victimsâ¢ means the people, whose life, health or property have suffered from a disaster;

Article 5. Main Principles of Disaster Protection Activities
* 1.The next principles shall be followed in disaster protection activities:
<\li1>
	* Timely execution of measures aimed at disaster prevention, rescue, response or recovery;
	* In planning and carrying out disaster protection measures, to take into consideration population and industrial location, their density and concentration, weather conditions, industrial and technological specifics, scale of real threat posed by the disaster;
	* To execute comprehensively the measures aimed at ensuring disaster preparedness;
	* Organization of disaster protection activities regardless of forms ownership;
	* To coordinate the collaboration of governmental organizations, NGOs and the general public;

Article 7. Disaster Protection Training
* The goal of the disaster protection training is to train and retrain relating organizations, services, officials and citizens in disaster prevention, rescue, response and recovery.
* The disaster protection training shall be classified as training for senior officials; rescue units, teams and branches; specialized units; students and pupils; employed and unemployed citizens.
* The disaster protection training shall be organized by the following organizations and officials:
	* The state administrative organization in charge of disaster protection shall organize training for its officials, managers of the state, Aimag and capital disaster protection services;
	* Heads and Staffs of the Aimag and capital disaster protection services shall organize training for the managers of Soum, district, entities and enterprises disaster protection services, heads of specialized units and citizens occupying positions similar to them;
	* Governors of Soum, district, bag and khoroo and heads of enterprises and organizations shall organize the training for the disaster protection personnel of the Soum, district, bag and khoroo, entities and enterprises;
	* Heads of corresponding rescue units, teams and branches, as well as specialized units shall organize training for the personnel of rescue units, teams and branches;
	* The training of students and pupils shall be organized by the State Administrative Central Agency in charge of education based on the lesson plans of the corresponding school.
	* The training for other people shall be organized by governors of bag and khoroo.

Article 7. Disaster Protection Training
* The goal of the disaster protection training is to train and retrain relating organizations, services, officials and citizens in disaster prevention, rescue, response and recovery.
* The disaster protection training shall be classified as training for senior officials; rescue units, teams and branches; specialized units; students and pupils; employed and unemployed citizens.
* The disaster protection training shall be organized by the following organizations and officials:
	* The state administrative organization in charge of disaster protection shall organize training for its officials, managers of the state, Aimag and capital disaster protection services;
	* Heads and Staffs of the Aimag and capital disaster protection services shall organize training for the managers of Soum, district, entities and enterprises disaster protection services, heads of specialized units and citizens occupying positions similar to them;
	* Governors of Soum, district, bag and khoroo and heads of enterprises and organizations shall organize the training for the disaster protection personnel of the Soum, district, bag and khoroo, entities and enterprises;
	* Heads of corresponding rescue units, teams and branches, as well as specialized units shall organize training for the personnel of rescue units, teams and branches;
	* The training of students and pupils shall be organized by the State Administrative Central Agency in charge of education based on the lesson plans of the corresponding school.
	* The training for other people shall be organized by governors of bag and khoroo.
* The training for personnel of the state administrative organization in charge of disaster protection, rescue units, teams, branches, specialized units, students, pupils, employed and unemployed citizens shall be provided once a year; the training for senior officials of the state, Aimag, Soum, district, bag and khoroo disaster protection services shall be held once every 2 years.
<\li1>

Article 8. Levels of Disaster Protection Readiness
* The disaster protection organizations, services, state and local administrations, entities and enterprises have the following levels of readiness:
	* Everyday readiness;
	* High level of readiness;
	* All-out readiness;
	* The following measures shall be carried out at the level of everyday readiness:
	* To develop and follow a disaster protection plan, taking into consideration the territorial and technological specifics;
	* Keep the means of communication and information dissemination ready to work, to train the population to act according to predetermined signals;
	* Promote the disaster prevention measures;
	* Re-equip the disaster protection rescue units, teams, branches and specialized units with manpower, machinery and equipment and step up their preparedness;
	* Improve the disaster protection training and exercises;
	* Form disaster protection reserves;
	* In everyday readiness the state, local administrations, entities and enterprises could be shifted to a special work regime during a disaster situation or a possible disaster. The procedure of special work regime should be established by the state administrative organization in charge of disaster protection
	* The following measures shall be carried out at the level of high level of readiness:
	* Introduction of clarifications in the disaster protection plan and dissemination of the warning signals to the population;
	* Shift the administrative-territorial management, and staff personnel to their disaster time duties;
	* Shift the headquarters, information and communication facilities to the state of everyday readiness;
	* Raise public awareness, receive and transmit any information directly, and disseminate the warning signals and information to organizations and the population permanently;
	* Mobilize manpower, machinery and materials and carry out joint exercises and training for supervisors, disaster protection staffs and search and rescue units, teams, branches and specialized units;
	* Impose quarantine;
	* Increase the reserves of materials and equipment;
	* During the all-out readiness level the following measures shall be carried out:
	* limit, for the period of time, the activities of the industry and service organizations other than nationwide and local communications, energy, public utilities, petrol stations and strategic organizations;
	* Authorities of the disaster protection organizations and services, their Staff, rescue units, teams, branches and specialized units as well as respective administrative-territorial units shall fully implement the planned measures for rescue of the population from disaster and its mitigation;
	* In case of shifting to all-out readiness level directly, the activities that should be undertaken during high level of readiness shall be undertaken simultaneously with other activities.

The disaster affected area shall be determined as following:
* The boundaries for the disaster affected area in the territory of Soums and districts should be determined by the governor of the respective Soums and districts;
* The boundaries of the disaster affected area covering territory in more than 2 Soums or districts should be determined by the Governor of the respective Aimag or capital;
* The boundaries of the disaster affected area in territories of Aimag, capital and several Aimags, should be determined by the Government based on a request from the Governor of the respective Aimag, capital and the conclusion of the state administrative organization in charge of disaster protection;

In order to coordinate the activities of disaster prevention, rescue, response and recovery the following disaster protection non-official state services supported by related state administrative organization shall be created
* Natural and chemical danger assessment and information service;
* Health protection service;
* Food and agriculture service;
* Infrastructure service;
* Order service;
* Public awareness and information service;
* Fire fighting service;
* Radiation protection service.
* To plan and organize the implementation of the disaster protection activities within the framework of the engaged section;
* To ensure the execution of laws and resolutions of higher authorities related to the disaster protection;
* To establish the management for disaster protection service, staff and specialized unit according to the specifics of the engaged section and to organize their training and preparedness;
* To ensure unaltered essential services of engaged section during the disaster situation;
* To keep the warning information systems of the engaged section constantly ready;
* To form the reserves of the machinery, equipment and tools for preventing and responding to damages caused by a disaster situation and keep them ready;
* To provide disaster protection services in Aimags and capital city with the professional management of engaged section;
	* 1.8.To immediately inform state administrative organization in charge of disaster protection on disaster situation and get their professional support;
<\li2>
	* To involve the professionals and machinery, equipment and tools of the engaged section in the operational staff dispatching to disaster site;
	* To dispose of funds allocated for a disaster according to the purpose;
	* To assess the damages caused by the disaster and to detail accordingly the proposals on measures to be taken;
	* To provide information and reports on the disaster situation

The Government of Mongolia shall exercise the following powers on disaster protection that are not provided in other legislation:
* To submit the draft of disaster protection program of Mongolia for the consideration of the Parliament, to take the measures in order to implement it.
* To adopt the regulation on forming and disposing of disaster reserves.
* To develop the state policy on the disaster protection and direct disaster protection nationwide activities;
* To submit to the Government the plans on disaster prevention, rescue of human lives and properties, response and recovery measures, and impose monitoring on the implementation of them;
* To provide state disaster protection mobilization and to propose to the Government the grounds for shifting to the disaster protection readiness in accord with the article 9.5.3 of this law;

The Prime Minister shall exercise the following powers:
* To propose to the Government the issue on allocating additional expenditures from Government Reserves and some material and equipment from the State Reserves for the measures of disaster prevention, rescue of human lives and properties, response and recovery;
* To make the decision on disposing of disaster protection reserves.
* To organize activities to implement the state policy, legislation and Governmental decisions on disaster protection, and to monitor the implementation of it;
* To coordinate the state and local executive bodyâ¢s activities in the frame of organizing and taking measures for disaster prevention, rescue, response and recovery;
* To support the activities of the disaster protection services and specialized units of state and local administrative authorities, economical units and organizations according to the regulations adopted by the Government;
* To organize the formation of disaster reserves in state and local administrative authorities, related entities and enterprises and branches and restore it;
* To organize disaster protection training at the national level;
* To implement of disaster protection activities with the methodological management at national level;
* To get the information and reports necessary for executing the disaster protection activities from state and local administrative authorities and disaster protection services of state, Aimag and capital city, to create a disaster database;
* To manage the activities of distributing disaster reserves released by the decision of the Prime Minister and the humanitarian aid provided by other countries, international organizations, foreign and local organizations, legal entities and individuals within the framework of civil protection to the victims;
* To cause an authorized body to do the vulnerability and risk assessment for entities and enterprises;
* To monitor the execution process of disaster protection activities taken by state and local authorities;
* To analyze the practices of using the legislation on disaster protection and accordingly to present to the authorized body itâ¢s improved version of the proposal;
* To communicate with the related foreign and international companies on disaster protection matters and to develop the cooperation;
* To communicate with the non governmental organizations on disaster protection matters;
* Other powers given by the legislation and government..

The head of State Administrative Organization in charge of disaster protection shall exercise the following full powers:
* To determine the structure and the organization of the disaster protection services of the State, Aimag, capital city, district, bag, khoroo, entities and enterprises, the operational staff, resources and dislocate them and to plan and carry out the measures providing their preparedness;
* To provide the President of Mongolia, the Speaker of the Great Khural and the Prime Minister with information on the disaster situation;
* To define the obligations of disaster protection services of State, Aimag, capital city, district, bag and khoroo if the legislation does not stipulate otherwise;
* To mobilize from the local area the manpower, machinery and material necessary for providing the activities of disaster prevention, rescue, response and recovery at the disaster site according to the decision of the Prime Minister;
* To inform the population on the hazards of the disaster, to create a common information system of disaster protection management;
* To train the population for disaster protection measures, to form disaster reserves and to monitor itâ¢s restoring;
* To dispose the approved budget of the State Administrative Organization in charge of disaster protection according to the related procedure;
* To represent the organization in local and foreign relations;
* To approve the structure, organization and vacancy for subordinating branches of State Administrative Organization in charge of disaster protection;
* To approve the regulations and guidance related to the disaster protection;
* To designate, dismiss and promote the heads and officers of divisions and subordinating branches of State Administrative Organization in charge of disaster protection;
* Other full powers given by the legislation and government.
* To plan, finance, manage and carry out the disaster protection activities at the administrative and territorial level;
* To shift to the disaster readiness level according to the Law;
* To create the disaster protection service, staff and specialized units according to the specifics of the related areas and to train them to be competent to fulfill their duties during the disaster situation;

The governors of Aimag, capital city, Soum, district, bag and khoroo shall exercise the following full powers:
* 1.4.To create a source of budget essential during the disaster situation and to dispose it;
<\li2>
	* To provide the higher authorities and the State Administrative Organization in charge of the disaster protection with the information on the disaster situation and carry out activities and to get professional consultation, instruction and support;
	* To insure the implementation of the disaster protection legislation and higher authority decisions;
	* To mobilize the manpower and machinery at the administration and territory level during the disaster situation;
	* To insure normal activities of the rescue teams, units, branches, services and specialized units;
	* To keep the communication and warning information systems constantly ready;
	* To assess the damages caused by the disaster and to elaborate accordingly the proposals on measures to be taken;
	* To urgently inform the higher authority of the information on the disaster situation;
	* Other full powers given by the legislation.
	* To elaborate, approve and implement a disaster protection plan;
	* To create the disaster protection non-official staff, service, and specialized units according to the specifics of own activity;
	* To supply the specialized units with necessary machinery and materials;
	* To train the specialized units and the personnel in the disaster protection activities in order to make them competent to work in the disaster site and to be prepared;
	* To execute and implement laws and regulations related to disaster protection issued by the authorized organization;
	* To render the vulnerability and risk assessment of disaster;
	* To create a source of budget necessary in time of a disaster and to dispose it according to the purpose;
	* To adjust the duties of the Disaster Protection Staff and specialized units to the needs of disaster time;
	* To provide the related higher authorities with the urgent information regarding the disaster

Entities and enterprises shall be responsible for following the disaster protection activities regardless of their jurisdiction, kind of property and type:
* To execute and implement the laws and regulations on the disaster protection issued by the authorized body;
* To participate in the disaster protection training and other organized measures;
* To respect and follow the safety requirements in private life and everyday activities, the industrial, technological discipline and ecological safety requirements;
* To recognize the disaster protection warning and information signals and be aware to act accordingly, possess the self-protection skills;
* To assist people who have suffered by the disaster and participate in activities to protect properties;
* To learn the use of personal and public protection tools designed to protect from disaster;
* To participate in the disaster prevention, rescue, response and recovery activities according to the approved procedure;
* To provide the related executive body with the urgent information on the disaster situation.
* To receive food, staff, special purpose clothing and rescue material, equipment and tools, self-protection means during the disaster work time participation in training and the implementation of duty.
* To proceed freely to the related object for the disaster response activities;
* To get free medical services and treatment for injuries and disabilities received while carrying out disaster prevention, rescue, response and recovery activities,
* To be ready for disaster prevention, rescue, response and recovery activities,

The disaster protection serviceman shall be responsible for following duties aside from the general duties of state serviceman indicated in the law on State Service:
* To execute the disaster prevention, rescue, response and recovery activities in accordance with the technical specifications and safety requirements;
* To give instructions and to provide professional support to the organizations, officers and citizens participating in disaster prevention, rescue, response and recovery activities at the disaster site;
* To follow the discipline regulations of a disaster protection serviceman
* 2.The benefits shall be paid to the citizen or to his/her family the same as to disaster protection serviceman in case of temporary or permanent disability or loss of life during the participation in the activities for disaster prevention, rescue, response and recovery and training.

Elements breached disaster protection legislation shall be liable to the following administrative penalties, if the breach does not constitute a criminal offence:
* Entities and enterprises breaching the Articles 7.3.2-7.3.6 of this law shall be imposed fines of up to 150000-250000 tugrugs and officials up to 40000-60000 tugrigs;
* Entities and enterprises breaching the Articles 11.3 and 11.4 of this law shall be imposed fines of up to 150000-250000 tugrugs, officials up to 30000-60000 tugrugs and individuals up to 5000-25000;
* Entities and enterprises breaching the articles 18, 26, 27, 28 of this law shall be imposed fines of up to 100000-250000 tugrugs, officials up to 30000-60000 tugrugs and individuals up to 10000-25000 tugrugs.
